<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3442100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 22. A. Phorcus sp., Silicone cast of MGUH 33109. Exposed width 2.2 mm. B–C. Stomatella sp., External mould of MGUH 33110. Figure B has been colour inverted and mirrored to show it in positive. Width 1.5 mm. D–F. Solariella sp. D–E. Silicone cast of MGUH 33111. Width 6.2 mm. F. Silicone cast of aperture of MGUH 33112. Width 5.95 mm. G–I. Skenea sp. G–H. Inner mould of MGUH 33113. Width 5.2 mm. I. Inner mould of MGUH 33114. Width 10.2 mm. J–K. Leucorhynchia sp., Silicone cast of MGUH 33115. Width 2.4 mm. L–N. Tectus? indecorus n. sp., L. Umbilical view of inner mould of paratype ØSM.10042-327-b. Width 19.7 mm. M–N. Silicone cast of holotype MGUH 33116. Width 1.7 mm. O–P. Homalopoma sp., Silicone cast and inner mould of MGUH 33117. Width 9.6, 6.9 mm respectively. Q. Calliomphalus (Calliomphalus) sp., Silicone cast of MGUH 33118. Width 3.1 mm. R–U. Arene jakobseni n. sp. R–T. Silicone cast of holotype MGUH 33119. Width 8.6 mm. U. Silicone cast of paratype MGUH 33120. Width of aperture 4.8 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3442100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

